    "total_efficiency_score": 781.1,
    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling output today, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (74.83) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (70.56), our two highest-projected starters. **Yordan Alvarez** remains the focal point of the lineup, boasting an elite 0.436 xwOBA that justifies his place in the middle of our order regardless of the opponent. Meanwhile, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from a distinct platoon advantage that pushes his efficiency score well into the \"Strong\" tier, effectively mitigating a slight wind-in warning at his stadium. In the leadoff spot, **Trea Turner** (62.50) is a high-priority start; his ability to exploit Eury P\u00e9rez\u2019s slow delivery significantly boosts his stolen base floor, a critical metric given our organizational focus on filling that scarcest of categories.\n\nWhile the lineup is robust, **Kazuma Okamoto** (64.30) and **Junior Caminero** (62.35) provide essential depth against favorable SP_xERA matchups above 4.00. The most difficult decision at the margins was excluding **Jerar Encarnacion** (48.03) and **Colt Keith** (46.55). **Jerar Encarnacion** was the primary consideration for the bench-to-starter transition, but the optimizer ultimately prioritized the superior lineup placement and platoon efficiency of **Carson Benge** (58.95) and **Josh Smith** (59.04). With **Christian Yelich** remaining sidelined on the IL, we are managing our depth carefully, though we remain wary of the volatility introduced by several \"Lineup Pending\" designations across the board. We will monitor the official cards closely; any late-afternoon shifts for **Dillon Dingler** or **Caleb Durbin** could force a pivot to **Colt Keith** if their projected order drops significantly.",
